12. AUTISM-SPECIFIC DESIGN CONSIDERATIONS
12.1 Sensory-Friendly Design
Principles:

No autoplay videos with sound (unless user initiates)
No flashing or strobing animations
Subtle, gentle animations (puzzle pieces float slowly)
High contrast for readability
Option to reduce motion (respect prefers-reduced-motion)
Clear, simple navigation
Minimal distractions

12.2 Inclusive Language
Guidelines:

Person-first and identity-first language both acceptable
"Crian√ßas autistas" OR "crian√ßas com autismo"
Focus on strengths and abilities
Avoid infantilizing language
Celebrate neurodiversity
Acknowledge challenges without negativity

12.3 Visual Elements
Autism Symbolism:

Puzzle pieces: Traditionally associated with autism awareness
Rainbow infinity symbol: Neurodiversity symbol (consider including)
Dragon: Friendly, playful mascot representing strength and uniqueness
Use diverse, inclusive imagery of children


